The Chronicle Prosper Ndlovu in MAUN, BOTSWANA The 2nd Botswana-Zimbabwe Bi-National Commission (BNC) has come to an end here in Maun, Botswana with the two countries reaffirming their commitment to scale up bilateral cooperation for the mutual benefit of their economies and steer regional integration interests. President Emmerson Mnangagwa and his Botswana counterpart, Dr Mokgweetsi Masisi presided over the closing session this afternoon, after four days of engagements, which saw the two countries signing seven MoUs and agreements that cover a wide range of socio-economic development aspects. <img class="alignnone wp-image-488856 size-article-featured-image" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/02/DSC_0126-675x380.jpg" alt="" width="675" height="380" /> The seven MoUs cover cultural cooperation, sport development, health matters, media information and publicity, provision of affordable and functional low-cost housing, education and training as well as employment and labour. These add to the six agreements signed in the inaugural BNC, that was held in Harare last year. In their remarks the two leaders stressed the need to expedite implementation of the agreements to ensure tangible benefits to citizens from both states. <img class="alignnone wp-image-488858 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/02/DSC_0168.jpg" alt="" width="674" height="318" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/02/DSC_0168.jpg 674w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/02/DSC_0168-360x170.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px" /> They also emphasised the need to speed up completion of join infrastructure projects, increased synergies on clean energy generation, environmental cooperation and unlocking earnings from the rich wildlife resource among others. President Mnangagwa attended the conference with nine Cabinet ministers and senior government officials who arrived earlier for preliminary talks. Zimbabwe will host the next BNC in 2021.